  "text": "As shown by NullAway and other recent work [CITATION_1] , developers are willing to use pluggable type systems, even with a moderate annotation burden, to prevent mobile application crashes, due to the difficulty of addressing such crashes in production. The type systems need not be fully sound, as long as they provide reasonably strong safety guarantees in practice. We believe that developing type systems with soundness tradeoffs similar to NullAway for other common types of crashes (e.g., array indexing errors) is a fruitful area for future research. Beyond investigating such systems, we are actively researching improved nullability type inference for libraries, to further increase the safety of NullAway-checked code.",
